      <h3 class='article'>
        <a name="textiles"></a>
        Qing Dynasty
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=3356' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Qīng', 'Qing Dynasty')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>清</a>
      </h3>
      <p>
        We know a lot about clothing in the Qing Dynasty because much of it was preserved and there is an abundant amount
        of written information and pictures.
        Some of the most interesting items of clothing during the Qing are those worn by the members of the Qing court.
        Because of its location, the Capital Museum in Beijing has a number of excellent items used by Qing emperors
        and others closely connected with him.
        The picture below shows an imperial table cover from the Qianlong reign (1736&mdash;1795). 
      </p>
      <a name="dragon"></a>
      <div class="picture">
        <a href='illustrations_use.php?mediumResolution=tablecloth_qing400.jpg'><img class='use' src='images/tablecloth_qing400.jpg' alt='to embroider' title='to embroider'/></a>
        <div>
          <div class='picture_header'><a href='/word_detail.php?id=5355' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '黃 huáng', 'yellow')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">黄</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=14527' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '緞 duàn', 'satin')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">缎</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=13529' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '繡 xiù​', 'to embroider')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">绣</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=3371' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'jīn', 'metal / gold')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">金</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=1818' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '龍 lóng', 'dragon')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">龙</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=5989' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'zhuō', 'table')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">桌</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=3493' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '圍 wéi', 'to circle / to surround')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">围</a></div>
          <a href='/word_detail.php?id=3355' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'qīng', 'clear / distinct / complete / pure')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">清</a> <a href='/word_detail.php?id=8474' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Qián Lóng', 'Qian Long')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">乾隆</a>（1736〜1795年）<a href='/word_detail.php?id=737' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Běijīng', 'Beijing')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">北京</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=2887' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'shǒudū​', 'capital city')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">首都</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=3974' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '博物館 bówù​guǎn', 'Museum')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">博物馆</a>
          <div class='picture_header'>Yellow satin embroidered table cover with golden dragon design</div>
          Qianlong Reign, Qing (1736&mdash;1795), Capital Museum, Beijing
        </div>
      </div>
      <p>
        The picture below shows a <span class='bookTitle'>dragon robe</span> <a href='/word_detail.php?id=18954' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '龍袍 lóng​ páo', 'the emperor&apos;s court dress')" 
        onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>龙袍</a>, which was the emperor's court dress.
        Golden dragons are embroidered on, as shown in the detail, right.
        Also, notice the longevity character <a href='/word_detail.php?id=6238' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '壽 shòu', 'life / long life')" 
        onmouseout="hideToolTip()">寿</a> to the left of the dragon.
        The pattern is a traditional <span class='bookTitle'>dragon playing with a pearl</span> <a href='/word_detail.php?id=26298' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '龍戲珠 lóng xì zhū', 'a dragon playing with a pearl')" 
        onmouseout="hideToolTip()">龙戏珠</a> design.
        A common related design is <span class='bookTitle'>two dragons playing with a pearl</span> <a href='/word_detail.php?id=26297' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '二龍戲珠 èr lóng xì zhū', 'two dragons playing with a pearl')" 
        onmouseout="hideToolTip()">二龙戏珠</a>.
        These designs refer to a early Chinese literature and legend in
        <span class='bookTitle'>Zhuang Zi</span> <a href='/word_detail.php?id=9741' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '莊子 Zhuāng Zǐ', 'Zhuang Zi')" 
        onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>庄子</a> (369-286 BCE), an influential Chinese philosopher who lived during the Warring States Period,
        and others.
      </p>
      <a name="dragon_robe"></a>
      <div class="picture">
        <a href='illustrations_use.php?mediumResolution=dragon_robe_qing400.jpg'><img class='use' src='images/dragon_robe_qing400.jpg' alt='Dragon robe' title='Dragon robe'/></a>
        <div>
          <div class='picture_header'><a href='/word_detail.php?id=25888' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'píngjīn', 'flat gold embroidery')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">平金</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=25898' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '納紗 nà shā', 'petit-point')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">纳纱</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=13529' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '繡 xiù​', 'to embroider')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">绣</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=18954' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '龍袍 lóng​ páo', 'the emperor\'s court dress')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">龙袍</a></div>
          <a href='/word_detail.php?id=4192' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Qīngcháo', 'Qing Dynasty')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">清朝</a>（<a href='/word_detail.php?id=8496' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'gōngyuán', 'AD / Christian era')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">公元</a>1644〜1911<a href='/word_detail.php?id=438' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'nián', 'year')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">年</a>） <a href='/word_detail.php?id=737' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Běijīng', 'Beijing')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">北京</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=2887' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'shǒudū​', 'capital city')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">首都</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=3974' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '博物館 bówù​guǎn', 'Museum')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">博物馆</a>
          <div class='picture_header'>Dragon robe with flat gold petit-point embroidery</div>
          Qing (1644&mdash;1911), Suzhou Silk Museum
        </div>
      </div>
      <p>
        A <span class='bookTitle'>rank badge</span> <a href='/word_detail.php?id=25889' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '官補 guān bǔ', 'a rank badge / an official badge')" 
        onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>官补</a> or mandarin square is a large embroidered badge sewn onto an official robe in 
        Imperial China.
        They were first used in the Ming and continued to be used in the Qing but with different designs.
        The picture below shown a <span class='bookTitle'>rank badge</span> with an embroidered crane design, indicating that 
        the person who wore it was a top ranking civilian official.
      </p>
      <a name="crane"></a>
      <div class="picture">
