          <div class='picture_header'>Lady's jacket with round crane design</div>
          Qing (1644&mdash;1911), Suzhou Silk Museum
        </div>
      </div>
      <p>
        The emperor wore a <span class='bookTitle'>dragon robe</span> <a href='/word_detail.php?id=18954' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '龍袍 lóngpáo', 'the emperor&apos;s court dress')" 
        onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>龙袍</a> in court, a <span class='bookTitle'>mian robe</span> <a href='/word_detail.php?id=25887' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'miǎnfú', 'mian robe / emperor&apos;s ceremonial dress')" 
        onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>冕服</a> at certain ceremonies, and <span class='bookTitle'>tongtian ceremonial costume</span> <a href='/word_detail.php?id=26205' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'tōng tiān guān fú', 'tongtian ceremonial costume')" 
        onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>通天冠服</a> for the highest ceremonies.
        <span class='bookTitle'>Yuanyou ceremonial costume</span> <a href='/word_detail.php?id=26206' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '遠遊冠服 yuǎn yóu guān fú', 'yuanyou ceremonial costume')" 
        onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>远游冠服</a> was the full custume worn by princes at ceremonies.
        <span class='bookTitle'>Court dress</span> <a href='/word_detail.php?id=26204' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'cháofú', 'court dress')" 
        onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>朝服</a> was worn by high officials during important events and ceremonies.
      </p>
